    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Using Workspace Files</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The contents of a </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Workspace</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can be saved to a file using the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">File/Save</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> menu command so your actions can be reloaded and possibly replayed later at a later date. You can open a workspace on a text &#160;file by choosing </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">File/Open</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> in any tool.</text></para>
  </body>
